The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Thursday, May 13, 2004  Nation at a Glance				 																Nine die as express rams into tempoBallia (PTI): Nine persons were killed and three seriously injured when the Sadbhavana Express rammed into a tempo at an unmanned railway crossing between Phefana and Sagarpali stations on Wednesday.				 																																																										The train, on its way to New Delhi from Muzaffarpur in Bihar, hit the tempo ferrying passengers about 8 km from here, killing eight people on the spot, superintendent of police Sanjay Tarde said.				 																																																										One of the injured died in the hospital, the officer said, adding that the victims were reported to be members of a marriage party. The railway traffic on the route was disrupted for some time. 				 																																																										Uttar Pradesh chief minister Mulayam Singh Yadav has granted an ex-gratia payment of Rs 1 lakh to the kin of each of the deceased and Rs 50,000 to each injured, Tarde said.				 																India backs Pak entry to forumYogyakarta (Indonesia) (AFP): India on Wednesday endorsed Pakistans application to join the Asean Regional Forum (ARF) after an assurance that Islamabad would not use it as a platform to raise bilateral issues such as Kashmir.				 																																																										Officials from the 23-member forum agreed to admit Pakistan and will recommend the decision to their ministers who will meet in Jakarta in early July.				 																																																										Officials recommend that ARF ministers approve Pakistans admission as an ARF participant, taking into account this formal and solemn assurance from Pakistan, said Indonesian foreign ministry spokesman Marty Natalegawa.				 																																																										Pakistan has given an assurance through Indonesia that it will not raise Indian-Pakistani bilateral issues at the ARF, Natalegawa said.				 																																																										At Wednesdays meeting, India demanded that the Pakistani assurance be mentioned in the recommendation, Natalegawa added.				 																																																										He said the officials agreed to invite Pakistan to attend the Jakarta meeting on July 1-2.				 																																																										The forum includes the 10 Asean countries and partners  Australia, Canada, China, the European Union, India, Japan, South and North Korea, Mongolia, New Zealand, Papua New Guinea, Russia, and the US.				 																Maid dead at Sajjan houseNew Delhi (PTI): A maidservant was found dead at the residence of the Congress Lok Sabha candidate from Outer Delhi, Sajjan Kumar, on Wednesday, police sources said.				 																																																										Manisha, 19, was found dead in the servants bathroom at Kumars house in north-west Delhis Paschim Vihar. Manisha appeared to have been electrocuted.				 																Globe rap on govtNew Delhi (PTI): Delhi High Court has expressed unhappiness over the Centre not properly investigating the sale of Chinese globes that do not show Jammu and Kashmir as a part of India. The court has asked the central government to probe the matter and submit a report within two weeks.				 																School racketAhmedabad (PTI): Three persons have been arrested in the multi-crore dummy student and teacher case on Wednesday, taking the total number of those arrested to six. Holy Child School is alleged to have siphoned off more than Rs 12-crore of government grants in over 10 years by showing dummy students on register and dummy teachers on muster. 				 																Devgun chargeMumabi (PTI): A court has asked police to investigate a cheating complaint filed by actor Ajay Devguns entertainment firm against ATN International Ltd and its directors to recover Rs 50 lakh. According to the complaint, Devguns firm had a pact with ATN International and Babul Arts for the telecast of TV serial Mukhosh. But ATN did not pay the guarantee money.				 																Salman car pleaMumbai (PTI): Almost two years after Salman Khan allegedly rammed his Land Cruiser jeep into a bakery killing one person and injuring four, the actor has moved a sessions court seeking return of the seized vehicle. Magistrate S.Y. Sishode will hear the plea on Thursday. 				 																House securityNew Delhi (PTI): A Rs 108-crore security apparatus has been put in place at the Parliament complex following the December 13, 2001, strike. The system will start working from the first session of the 14th Lok Sabha.																		Jodhpur, called the Sun City, organised a festival to celebrate the 546th foundation day of Marwars capital. The city, founded by Suryavanshi Rao Jodha, has given three chief ministers to Rajasthan  Jai Narayan Vyas, Barkatullah Khan and Ashok Gehlot. 
